article.description: Mamadou Ndiaye scored 13 points, had seven rebounds and blocked four shots to lead UC Irvine past Division III Chapman 65-51 Friday night.
article.headline: UC Irvine uses size advantage in 65-51 win over Ndiaye
article.linkText: UC Irvine uses size advantage in 65-51 win over Ndiaye
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. -- Mamadou Ndiaye scored 13 points, had seven rebounds and blocked four shots to lead UC Irvine past Division III Chapman 65-51 Friday night. The Anteaters started what is believed to be the tallest lineup in college basketball history with the 7-foot-6 Ndiaye, 7-2 Ioannis Dimakopoulos, 6-10 Mike Best, 6-10 Jonathan Galloway and 6-8 Shawn Ray. UC Irvine (8-4) blocked 13 shots. Despite the fact UC Irvine never trailed, James Taylor's layup with 4:10 remaining before halftime cut the Anteaters' lead to 24-22. But UC Irvine put together a 10-4 run before the break and led 34-26 at intermission. In the second half, a Dominique Dunning 3 and back-to-back layups from Wright made the score 44-33 with 16:35 to play. Wright's 3 with 3:55 left made the score 62-47. Cam Haslam scored 21 points for Chapman (4-3) and James Taylor added 12.
